# Every Dockerfile builds with context "." (repo root, see docker-compose.yml), then COPYs
# individual service directories in. Without this file, host-built bin/obj (containing
# Windows-absolute NuGet fallback paths from local `dotnet build`) get copied into the Linux
# build stage and clobber the in-container `dotnet restore` output, breaking `dotnet publish
# --no-restore` with MSB4018 "Unable to find fallback package folder ...NuGetPackages".
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/.vs/

.git/
.vscode/
BaseCore/

.env
.env.*
!.env.example

**/appsettings.Development.json
**/appsettings.*.local.json
**/secrets.json

**/node_modules/
FrontEnd/
sql/

*.user
*.suo
